---
Source:
  Title: The Complete Works of Chuang Tzu
  ID: 50ae0a98-5702-40cb-8c11-4c6297aa457a
  Translator: Burton Watson
By: Zhuangzi
Locus:
  Chapter: 13
  Paragraph: 26
Title: The Way Of Heaven
---
\"Of course," said Confucius. "If the gentleman lacks benevolence, he
will get nowhere; if he lacks righteousness, he cannot even stay alive.
Benevolence and righteousness are truly the inborn nature of man. What
else could they be?"
